How would you fix the race condition in this Rust code?
```rust
use std::sync::atomic::{AtomicBool, Ordering};

static READY: AtomicBool = AtomicBool::new(false);

fn writer() {
    // write data to shared memory
    READY.store(true, Ordering::Relaxed);
}

fn reader() {
    while !READY.load(Ordering::Relaxed) {}
    // read data from shared memory
}
```

output:
[High] Data-Race-Via-Relaxed-Ordering: `Ordering::Relaxed` does not establish a happens-before relationship. The reader may see `READY == true` before the writer's data writes are visible, reading stale or partial data.

Fix:
1. Use `Ordering::Release` on the store and `Ordering::Acquire` on the load
2. This ensures all writes before the store are visible to the reader after the load succeeds

```rust
use std::sync::atomic::{AtomicBool, Ordering};

static READY: AtomicBool = AtomicBool::new(false);

fn writer() {
    // write data to shared memory
    READY.store(true, Ordering::Release);
}

fn reader() {
    while !READY.load(Ordering::Acquire) {}
    // read data from shared memory — guaranteed to see writer's data
}
```

